Hi Milio,really nice job ! You can do even better: 
```text
$concept  = optional_param('concept', '', PARAM_CLEAN);


$courseid = optional_param('courseid', 
$COURSE->id
, PARAM_INT);


$eid      = optional_param('eid', 0, PARAM_INT); // glossary entry id


$displayformat = optional_param('displayformat',-1, PARAM_SAFEDIR);
```
 This will don't break Moodle core code more then your: when courseid is not provided it will be initialised with the value of the current course otherwise it will be used the value provided in the URL provided. Would you like to file an improvement into the Tracker? I guess, if confirmed, it could work even not with SCORM, whenever $COURSE is available. HTH, Matteo

